                    <physDesc>
                        <objectDesc>
                            <supportDesc>
                                <support><p>A marble plaque, intact on the left margin and above (although with an uneven edge), broken on the right and below; the text however appears to be complete and to follow the shape of the stone on the right margin.</p>
                                    <material ana="#material.stone.marble" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/material/lod/48.html">marble</material>
                                    <objectType ana="#object.plaque" ref="https://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/objtyp/lod/259.html">plaque</objectType>
                                    <dimensions><!-- from Orsi -->
                                        <height unit="cm">18</height>
                                        <width unit="cm">15</width>
                                        <depth unit="cm"/>
                                    </dimensions>
                                </support>
                                <condition ana="#condition.damaged"/>
		    </supportDesc>
                            <layoutDesc>
                                <layout><p>The text appears to observes the shape of the stone, with a fixed left margin and the lines fitting to the line of breakage on the right, and a staurogram centrally filling the space below. The letters retain traces of red paint throughout.</p>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.chiselled" ref="http://www.eagle-network.eu/voc/writing/lod/1">chiselled</rs>
                                    <rs ana="#execution.rubrication.red">Rubrication, red coloured</rs>
                                	<damage ana="#text_condition.complete"/>
			</layout>
                            </layoutDesc>
                        </objectDesc>
                        <handDesc>
                            <handNote><p>Slightly irregular but neatly carved plain letters without serifs. Alpha has straight bar; Epsilon is rectilinear, with mostly equal length bars; Theta is large and voice, with a full width horizontal bar; Kappa generally has short arms; Lamda has a slight extension at the top; Mu (in ligature) has vertical virst and last, with diagonals extending only half-way down;' rho has small head, closed; sigma is lunate but rectilinear; omega is lunate. Interpuncts are used around numerals.</p>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line1">Line 1</locus>
                                <dimensions type="letterHeight">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                                <locus from="line1" to="line2">Interlineation line 1 to 2</locus>
                                <dimensions type="interlinear">
                                    <height unit="mm"/>
                                </dimensions>
                            </handNote>
                        </handDesc>
